All-out efforts in search and rescue of the missing and treatment of the injured after a coal mine collapsed in Alxa League, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. The collapse has so far left two people dead, six injured, and more than 50 missing. All regions and related departments are identifying all types of risks and hidden dangers with a sense of responsibility, enhancing prevention measures and ensuring strict implementation to better coordinate development and safety. The Ministry of Emergency Management has sent a work team with 152 members and 32 vehicles to Inner Mongolia to guide rescue work. On-site rescue work by local authorities is underway.